Package: satbathy
Title: Satellite-Derived Bathymetry with the Empirical Ratio Transform
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jean François", "Mas", , "jfmas@ciga.unam.mx", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Azucena", "Pérez Vega", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Tools to estimate water depth in shallow, low-turbidity
    coastal waters from multispectral satellite imagery (e.g. Landsat,
    Sentinel-2 and PlanetScope) using the empirical log-ratio transform of
    Stumpf, Holderied and Sinclair (2003)
    <doi:10.4319/lo.2003.48.1_part_2.0547>. The package provides water
    masking, sun-glint correction, spatial filtering, log-ratio
    computation, linear model fitting and prediction, iterative estimation
    of the maximum reliable depth, turbidity indexing for image selection,
    and accuracy assessment.
